I would use a directed graph. There are no directed graph classes in the JDK, but there are many libraries that implement it (listed [here](https://www.baeldung.com/java-graphs)), I would personally look at jgrapht or Google&#39;s Guava library (do not remember if there is a directed graph).
This is what a directed graph for your data looks like:  
[![Directed Graph][1]][1]

Once your directed graph is created, and you ensure it has no cycles (for example, you did not define A-B, B-C, C-A, which creates a cycle), then sorting is a just a matter of writing a comparator with the following logic:
 - if o1 == o2 return 0;
 - if o1 is connected to o2 return -1;
 - if o1 is not connected to o2 return 1;

